element.name: ID_BB_SEC_NUM_SRC
element.description: This is the unique realtime Bloomberg identifier.

element.name: FEED_SOURCE
element.description: Bloomberg identifier for the source of the information. The market data source is the exchange or pricing contributor mnemonic that uniquely identifies the market data originator. In the case of an NYSE listed security which trade on multiple exchanges, this would be the market center originator of the data, such as The Chicago Stock Exchange, The Archipelago Stock Exchange, or the NYSE. In the case of a composite market data source such the US composite for exchange-traded securities, it is possible to have a local market data source in addition to the composite data source. With a composite daily high price, the security reference may be the US composite (such as INTC US), and the exchange that generated the high price may be the Cincinnati Stock Exchange or NASDAQ. The local market data source is an optional field, so on non-composite securities, it will not be present -- only the MD.Source will be available.The MD.Source mnemonic will be the same as the exchange or contributor mnemonic on the Bloomberg professional in many cases, but is not guaranteed to match.In the case of contributor data the MD.Source mnemonic will be the same mnemonic for fixed income securities as the Price Contributor Source or PCS in many cases, but is not guaranteed to match. Contributed currency market data will have also use the XDF code in many cases, but is not guaranteed to match.

element.name: ID_BB_SEC_NUM_DES
element.description: This identifier is a string that uniquely identifies an instrument.

element.name: ID_BB_UNIQUE
element.description: Unique identifier assigned by Bloomberg to all securities.

element.name: PARSEKYABLE_DES_SOURCE
element.description: This identifier is the string that can be entered into the Bloomberg professional to uniquely select this security.This description includes the source of the security. The parsekeyable string has the 'at sign' in it when the security has multiple sources. This is available for fixed income and currency objects. The format is 'ticker at sign pcs yellowkey'. To view on the Bloomberg professional replace the 'at sign' with a space. Equities, index options, currency options, future options and indices have parsekeyable string 'ticker source yellowkey'. Equity options do not have a parsekeyable string.As for How many spaces exist between the PCS code and the yellow key for Reference.Security.ID.ParsekeyableDescription? This is a 4 character field regardless of the PCS code. For PCS codes that contain 3 letters, there will be 2 spaces before the yellow key. For PCS codes that contain 4 letters, there will only be 1 space.

element.name: LAST_UPDATE
element.description: Either the time or date at which the security last traded/updated. All values are translated into the user's date and time. If the last trade/update occurred today, it will show the time of the trade/update, otherwise it will show the date on which the security last traded/updated.

element.name: PRICING_SOURCE
element.description: Acronym or short code for the market pricing source. Returns are based on the user's settings. If there is no price from the chosen source, the next available source will be used.

element.name: OPT_ADJ_CONTRACT
element.description: Returns 'Y' if the contract terms have been adjusted. This usually occurs due to a merger, split, or other corporate action

element.name: OPT_EXER_TYP
element.description: There are three ways an option can be exercised: American Style, Bermuda Style and European Style.

element.name: FEED_DELAYED_EID1
element.description: Entitlement identifier for the level one delayed data feed.

element.name: BPIPE_REFERENCE_SECURITY_CLASS
element.description: Top level asset class designation for the reference security event on the B-Pipe feed.

element.name: FUT_MONTH_YR
element.description: The month and year of contract expiration

element.name: ID_EXCH_SYMBOL
element.description: Local exchange security symbol.

element.name: LAST_TRADEABLE_DT
element.description: Last date that the contract is available for trade.

element.name: FUT_TRADING_SESSION
element.description: Determines if the data displayed for a contract is from that contract's day or night session. Does not apply to all contracts.

element.name: CRNCY
element.description: Currency in which the security was issued.

element.name: GENERATION_NUMBER
element.description: Number created for new option series that are created after a capital adjustment. All new created series will get this number. The generation number stays unchanged for the lifetime of a series.

element.name: ID_FULL_EXCHANGE_SYMBOL
element.description: Contains the exchange symbol for futures and options, and indices inclusive of base symbol and other security elements.

element.name: ID_ISIN
element.description: A twelve-character number assigned by the local national numbering agency.

element.name: ID_CUSIP
element.description: Security identification number for the U.S. and Canada.

element.name: ID_MIC_LOCAL_EXCH
element.description: ISO Market Identification Code (MIC) of the local exchange on which this instrument is traded for equities

element.name: ID_MIC_PRIM_EXCH
element.description: ISO Market Identification Code (MIC) of the Bloomberg assigned primary exchange on which this specific security is traded.

element.name: NAME
element.description: Name of the company or brief description of the instrument.

element.name: SECURITY_TYP
element.description: Description of the specific instrument type within its market sector.

element.name: EXPIRATION_PERIODICITY
element.description: Specifies the periodicity of the option's expiration. Possible values are: D - Daily Expiration W - Weekly Expiration M - Monthly Expiration Q - End of Month Expiration (includes Quarter End Expirations)

element.name: TRADING_SYSTEM_IDENTIFIER
element.description: Unique identifier for the instrument, as used on the source trading system.

element.name: FUTURES_CATEGORY
element.description: The type of future (or option) the security is.

element.name: OPT_UNDL_EXP_DT
element.description: The expiration date of the option's underlying future.

element.name: ID_MIC1
element.description: ISO Market Identification Code (MIC) for the market on which the security trades.

element.name: EXCHANGE_ALTERNATIVE_IDENTIFIER
element.description: Exchange alternative identifier used in the exchange market data feed or system.

element.name: ISSUER_INDUSTRY
element.description: The industry classification of the issuer of the security.

element.name: TAPPED_INDICATOR
element.description: Returns 'Y' if the bond has been tapped or reopened allowing borrowers to sell bonds or other debt instruments from past issues.

element.name: MTY_TYP
element.description: Displays the bond's structure, i.e., Callable, Putable, Sinkable.

element.name: DAYS_TO_MTY_TDY
element.description: The number of days from today to the maturity date.

element.name: WEEK_NUMBER
element.description: Provides the numerical week number that the weekly option ticker represents in the month. Valid values are 0 when not applicable, 1 through 5 when applicable.

element.name: FLAG_144A
element.description: Returns a Y or N. An N also represents unknown or undisclosed.

element.name: MSCI_SEC_CODE
element.description: MSCI Security Code is a unique identifier assigned to each security by MSCI.

element.name: COUNTRY
element.description: Bloomberg country code of the issuer.

element.name: OPTION_ROOT_TICKER
element.description: The option root ticker symbol for equity options and equity index options.

element.name: MARKET_STATUS
element.description: Trading status of an equity.

element.name: CURRENT_CONTRACT_MONTH_YR
element.description: Month and year of the current contract, which can be futures, generics, spreads, or generic spreads.

element.name: FUT_CONT_SIZE
element.description: The smallest available value of tradable contract.

element.name: OPT_CONT_SIZE
element.description: Number of shares that can be exchanged for each option contract exercised.

element.description: This is the list identifier provided by the service.

element.name: EID

element.name: LIST_ACTION
element.description: Bitmap with information about how to deal with all the list of members pointed to by List.NextMember. Possible actions are: Clear = Delete all of the existing list members before adding any. Add = Add all the list members in this set. Delete = Delete all the list members in this set. Member IDs to be deleted must match exactly current member IDs. End = This is the last set in the sequence. Either Add or Delete, but not both, must be set. Clear should only be set with Add and for the first set of members in a list.
